OL,3,CWestminster committee urges Government
OL,4,Cto formally name Stakeknife
OL,6,FOperation Kenova, a probe which
OL,7,Fexamined the activities of Stakeknife,
OL,8,Fwho has been linked to at least 14
OL,9,Fmurders and 15 abductions, concluded
OL,10,Fthat more lives were probably lost
OL,11,Fthan saved through the operation of
OL,12,Fthe agent. However it was unable to
OL,13,Fconfirm Stakeknife's identity in its
OL,14,Ffinal report in December after the
OL,15,FGovernment refused its authorisation
OL,16,Fto do so.
OL,18,FSuccessive governments have refused to
OL,19,Fdo so, citing the long-standing policy
OL,20,Fof neither confirm nor deny (NCND).
