OL,3,CWestminster committee urges Government
OL,4,Cto formally name Stakeknife
OL,6,FThen, Northern Ireland Secretary
OL,7,FHilary Benn said the Government was
OL,8,Fconsidering its position on naming
OL,9,FStakeknife following a Supreme Court
OL,10,Fjudgment related to the disclosure of
OL,11,Fintelligence information in the case
OL,12,Fof the murder of Paul Thompson.
OL,14,FKenova chief Sir Iain Livingstone, and
OL,15,FPSNI Chief Constable Jon Boutcher, who
OL,16,Fpreviously led the investigation, have
OL,17,Furged the Government to name
OL,18,FStakeknife.
